    <h4>Frequently Asked Questions:</h4>
      <blockquote>
        <p><strong>Question:</strong> Can I set a limit on my donations for the month?<br>
        <strong>Answer:</strong> YES! Just visit your user profile, click on "edit info" and enter a new "Max donation. If you ever want to change or remove your donation limit, just visit this page again.</p><br>
        <p>
        <strong>Question:</strong> Does spareChange provide tax receipts for donations?<br>
        <strong>Answer:</strong> YES! You will receive a receipt in your email which has all the information you need for tax deductions.
        </p><br>
        <p>
        <strong>Question:</strong> What personal information do you store?<br>
        <strong>Answer:</strong> When you connect a bank account, we receive an encrypted token which allows us to query the amount of each transaction. We store that token, an encrypted token representing your account choice, encrypted tokens that represent your transactions and a customer ID for processing your donations. All of this information is stored on the server side and is inaccessible on the front end.</p>
      </blockquote>
